<p>For my desktop, I keep it obsessively clean. My app dock is always hidden by default and only pops up on mouse hover. This not only helps me focus on the app in use, limiting distraction, but it also allows me to appreciate the desktop artwork so much more. As for my wallpaper, I rotate between different designs in the <a href="https://minimalissimo.shop/product/slm-613-desktop" rel="noreferrer" target="_blank">SLM 613</a> set I made in collaboration with <a href="https://www.studiolenzing.com" rel="noreferrer" target="_blank">Studio Lenzing</a>. My main software tools are:</p>
