<h2>The physical desk</h2>
<p>The desk was not an easy one to source. I had ordered the first desk from <a href="https://lz-elements.com/shop/sinus-family" rel="noreferrer" target="_blank">L&amp;Z Elements</a> in Germany, but that was a couple of years ago when trade between the UK and EU was still in a transitional period. But since Brexit was finalised, it became a lot more challenging to source certain pieces of furniture—especially from small retailers. Anyway, I managed to find a UK producer of the linoleum finish. It was important to me to have matching desks. Although my new desk is a little smaller than the other, the depth and thickness are the same. It sits on two black Sinus trestle legs also sourced from L&amp;Z Elements.</p>
<figure class="img-figure"><div class="img-wrapper" data-tooltip="Minimal workspace setup 2022" style="padding-bottom: 150%"><img alt="Minimal workspace setup 2022" class="img" loading="lazy" src="https://carlbarenbrug.com/media/pages/blog/workspace-revisited-2022/2ba025e375-1690029239/2022-setup-4-2.jpg"></div></figure>
