            <pubDate>Tue, 03 Jun 2025 00:00:00 +0200</pubDate>
            <description><![CDATA[<p>The little creative lab I run with Manu, <a href="https://formfeelingfunction.com" rel="noreferrer" target="_blank">FormFeelingFunction&reg;</a>, is starting to take shape — albeit slowly. We’ve been mulling over all sorts of concepts. Some might be realised, some probably won’t, and a few definitely will. One that’s just gone live is our most experimental idea yet: a private audio guestbook.</p>
<figure class="img-figure with-caption"><div class="img-wrapper" data-tooltip="" style="padding-bottom: 100%"><img alt="" class="img" loading="lazy" src="https://carlbarenbrug.com/media/pages/blog/audio-guestbook/3e30a92a63-1750756799/fff-voicenote.jpg"></div><figcaption>Record a private voice note</figcaption></figure>
<p>It’s simple. You can leave us an anonymous voice note, up to 15 seconds long. Say whatever you want. It won’t be shared. It’s just for our ears.</p>
<p>We’re curious what kind of messages people will leave when there’s no public stage. Does knowing it’s private change what you share? Will it bring out something playful, serious, weird, or surprising? That’s the fun of it.</p>
<p>You can add your email if you want a reply, but you don’t have to. There are no rules here. We’ll keep the guestbook open for a while and see how it goes — it might become a permanent fixture, or we’ll open it only at certain times of the year. Time will tell. We’ll probably blog about what we learn, too.</p>
<p>So go ahead and drop us a voice note at <a href="https://formfeelingfunction.com" rel="noreferrer" target="_blank">formfeelingfunction.com</a></p>]]></description>
