<h2>The physical desk</h2>
<p>Unlike my previous desk from L&amp;Z Elements, my new desk was far simpler to source. It's the MITTZON adjustable standing desk from IKEA. I've wanted a standing desk for a long time, and most of them look the same, so I thought I'd just go with an affordable option that does the job well and invest more into other things. And the desk is actually decent. Admittedly, the finish of the tabletop is not at the same level as the L&amp;Z Sinus table, but it's far more practical for me. And it's bigger, so it feels really spacious. I continued the black aesthetic because I think it contrasts really well with some of the metallic accessories I have yet blends well with others.</p>
